    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of the species Salix nigra, native to eastern North America. It varies in color from almost white to brownish-yellow, and is important in the manufacture of artificial limbs. The young, long, pliable shoots are used for wicker baskets and furniture.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
